{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is cross-module handoff: three source clients -> aggregation/composition -> summary input payload. A unit test of only the formatter could miss dropped fields from one adapter. No real OS/network/subprocess is required to catch this specific failure; in-process fakes for the three source modules are sufficient. Rejected higher levels: System is disqualified because behavior text is about inclusion/handoff, not real network behavior; Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because correctness here does not depend on model judgment.","test_description":"Wire real aggregator/composer modules with stubbed source adapters returning distinct sentinel values per source, run report assembly, and assert the exact payload sent to summary generation contains all three source sections/keys.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is resilience behavior across module boundaries: source failure propagation -> section-level fallback rendering -> continued pipeline execution. Unit tests of a single fallback function are insufficient for real failure where orchestration might abort early. Real infrastructure is not strictly required: a source adapter fake that raises timeout/error can reproduce the behavior. Rejected higher levels: System is disqualified because behavior text does not require validating real network/OS semantics; Agentic/Workflow are disqualified because this is control-flow/fallback logic, not model-output quality.","test_description":"Run report generation with two source adapters returning data and one adapter raising a fetch error; assert process completes, output includes `data unavailable` in the failing section, and other sections remain populated.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on model output quality (faithful representation of values), which a deterministic stub would hide. The failure is not just wrapper logic; it is whether the real summarizer actually preserves/reflects key numbers and facts. Rejected Workflow: behavior text specifies a single summary-generation decision, not multiple agentic decisions in sequence.","test_description":"Feed controlled input data with critical numeric/text facts into the real summary-generation model and assert factual consistency constraints (key values present, no contradictions/hallucinated replacements) over repeated runs with acceptance thresholds.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.1}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure boundary includes real external I/O: API calls plus real email transport/inbox delivery. In-process mocks can pass while SMTP/provider auth, routing, MIME formatting, or deliverability fails in reality. Rejected Agentic/Workflow: behavior text validates end-to-end delivery to inbox, not quality of model decisions; any summary step can be fixed fixture content for this assertion.","test_description":"Execute scheduled script in a test environment against reachable test endpoints and a real mailbox, then verify the recipient inbox receives one message with expected subject/body/attachment structure.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.14,"System":0.72,"Agentic":0.08,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly spans real infrastructure boundaries: unreachable delivery service, filesystem persistence, and next scheduled execution. Mocking can hide real failures (file permission/path issues, scheduler/run-state persistence, network/connectivity error classes). Rejected Workflow: although multi-step over time, steps are infrastructure retry/persistence, not multiple agentic decisions.","test_description":"Run the script with email endpoint intentionally unreachable, assert report artifact is persisted on disk, then run the next scheduled invocation with service restored and verify queued report is sent and persistence state is cleared/updated correctly.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.18,"System":0.69,"Agentic":0.04,"Workflow":0.08}}]}
